Width \/ renderHeight;\nvar hFOV = 2 * Math.atan( Math.tan( vFOV \/ 2 ) * aspect );\nvar width  = 2 * Math.tan( ( hFOV \/ 2 ) ) * cameraPosition;\n```\n\nvFOV = 0.5829135889557342 which is also not a valid FOV\n\nCan you fill in the example for me and show an example that does give a valid FOV number?\nThe correct number of the above example is somewhere around 37\n","created_at":"2012-02-02T22:51:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1239#issuecomment-3788346","id":3788346,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/1239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3ODgzNDY=","updated_at":"2012-02-02T22:51:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/3788346","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1214701?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Tobiasartz","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMTQ3MDE=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Tobiasartz","type":"User","id":1214701,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Tobiasartz\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"In your fiddle,\n\nheight = height of your plane mesh = 500.\n\ndistance = camera.z - plane.z = 1000 - 100 = 900.\n\nvFOV = 2 \\* Math.atan( height \/ ( 2 \\* distance ) ) = 0.5419 radian